WEBVTT

00:44.244 --> 00:47.580
He had a black cat named
Macak when he was a boy.

00:52.835 --> 00:54.879
The cat followed him everywhere.

00:58.466 --> 01:01.469
And one day,
when he stroked the cat's back...

01:02.220 --> 01:03.680
... he saw a miracle.

01:06.099 --> 01:08.560
Light crackled under his hand.

01:10.853 --> 01:13.565
His father explained that
the lightning in the sky...

01:13.731 --> 01:17.235
... is like the sparks that
flew from Macak's back.

01:18.361 --> 01:20.113
And Tesla wondered

01:23.366 --> 01:26.369
Is Nature a Giant Cat?

01:26.536 --> 01:27.829
And if so:

01:30.123 --> 01:32.041
Who is stroking his back then?

01:39.716 --> 01:43.094
<font color="#FFFF00">NINE YEARS BEFORE

01:43.219 --> 01:46.639
EDISON MACHINE WORKS,
NEW YORK AUGUST 11, 1884

01:52.937 --> 01:55.940
The power of the thought.
Isn't that all about?

01:56.107 --> 01:58.443
The candles are there in the cupboard, right?

01:59.402 --> 02:03.197
Eventually we will be
able to see in the dark.

02:03.364 --> 02:04.699
I found them.

02:04.824 --> 02:07.994
I think there are more in the messy drawer.
Do you know where it is?

02:10.788 --> 02:12.999
The messy drawer?

02:13.166 --> 02:17.045
Aren't there cluttered
drawers where you come from?

02:17.212 --> 02:19.672
My mom had a messy drawer.
And yours?

02:19.839 --> 02:21.591
Leave my mother out.

02:22.800 --> 02:25.511
Nobody expected you
to come tonight, Tom.

02:25.678 --> 02:28.681
No?  Not really?

02:28.848 --> 02:30.516
I expected it.

02:34.687 --> 02:36.940
When I was five years old...

02:37.982 --> 02:40.777
Ed, you don't have to
stop because I'm talking.

02:44.155 --> 02:47.659
When I was five years old,
we sailed across Lake Erie...

02:47.825 --> 02:51.579
... to visit the
Edisons in Vienna.

02:51.746 --> 02:53.873
Vienna, Ontario.

02:54.040 --> 02:59.629
Mother and father. My sisters Marion and
Tannie. My brother Charlie. Grandpa Sam.

03:00.630 --> 03:02.382
I learned to swim.

03:03.383 --> 03:05.760
When I was back in Ohio...

03:05.927 --> 03:09.055
... I went out with
my good friend George.

03:09.180 --> 03:10.473
George Lockwood.

03:10.640 --> 03:12.350
He was my age.

03:12.517 --> 03:17.772
We went to a canal near my house.
I entered the water and George followed me.

03:17.939 --> 03:21.901
Afterwards I went home.
I felt numb and went to bed.

03:24.320 --> 03:27.156
When my mother woke me
up, it was very dark.

03:27.323 --> 03:29.033
She asked me about George.

03:30.159 --> 03:33.204
Everyone was looking for him.
Half the city.

03:33.371 --> 03:37.750
They lit lanterns, shouted his
name, and searched everywhere.

03:37.917 --> 03:42.338
I told her I saw George's head
disappear under the water...

03:42.505 --> 03:44.966
... and that I had waited a long time for him.

03:45.133 --> 03:47.093
I didn't know what to do.

03:49.304 --> 03:50.972
I was five years old.

03:53.349 --> 03:55.602
Why did I have to think about that now?

03:55.768 --> 03:57.645
Go home, Tom.  I mean it.

03:58.563 --> 04:00.982
I always assume that
people can swim.

04:02.442 --> 04:05.945
Hello, Tesla.
I haven't seen you there before.

04:08.448 --> 04:10.825
Is it true that you are from Transylvania?

16:34.580 --> 16:35.979
My God.

16:36.478 --> 16:40.390
Do not discuss this with the
conditional officer or physician.

16:40.491 --> 16:43.629
- I'm not talking.
- You can't get out of your life.

16:45.175 --> 16:47.257
Do you think it will be alright?

16:49.523 --> 16:52.483
Listen, you've had a lot.

16:53.400 --> 16:56.179
How can it be, I can't imagine.

16:56.572 --> 17:00.020
But you cannot live in the past.

17:00.892 --> 17:04.320
You slept as much as possible, which is what happened.

17:05.740 --> 17:07.423
You have to look ahead.

17:08.220 --> 17:09.434
Yes.

17:10.848 --> 17:12.246
You're right.

17:14.574 --> 17:16.771
Everything will be fine.

17:17.141 --> 17:19.287
Come on, let's get out of here.

17:56.474 --> 17:59.479
Hey? - I'm glad you
turned on the phone.

18:01.620 --> 18:03.620
I said I would wear it.

18:03.835 --> 18:05.096
Well done, Mary.

18:05.883 --> 18:08.468
- I hope everything will be fine.
- Thank you.

18:08.632 --> 18:09.901
Bye.

18:26.276 --> 18:28.209
Yes, Tom?

18:28.521 --> 18:30.810
You watched my daughter die.

18:33.059 --> 18:35.882
I'm going to look
at your death now.

19:14.043 --> 19:16.043
Hi.

19:33.601 --> 19:35.577
Rain is expected tonight.

19:36.440 --> 19:37.787
Maria.

19:39.138 --> 19:41.267
We've talked about this before.

19:42.274 --> 19:44.965
You can't panic
every time it rains.

19:46.645 --> 19:49.747
Do you know the 50's
song "Raindrops"?

19:50.398 --> 19:51.987
No.

19:54.496 --> 19:56.496
Raindrops.

19:57.362 --> 20:00.103
Lots of raindrops.

20:00.762 --> 20:02.738
It's like raindrops...

20:02.763 --> 20:05.163
OK PLEASE. Stop saying.

20:05.756 --> 20:07.914
Yes, I know that song.

20:10.794 --> 20:14.726
James calls me when
it rains and...

20:16.169 --> 20:18.507
... he played that
number on the phone.

20:21.976 --> 20:24.778
I knew it would kill someone.

20:26.500 --> 20:28.735
God, that's a terrible thing.

20:32.755 --> 20:35.745
Is that why you don't want a phone?

20:37.729 --> 20:39.633
This is one of many reasons.

20:43.490 --> 20:46.779
You were the only one
with me at this time.

20:49.822 --> 20:53.373
I couldn't have done
this without you.

20:55.887 --> 20:57.769
So thank you.

20:58.643 --> 21:00.831
You do not have to thank me.

21:01.445 --> 21:04.882
We have been friends since the age of five.
You're like one of my family.

21:06.740 --> 21:09.009
I'll never turn my back on you.

21:10.757 --> 21:12.999
I know what everyone
is saying about me.

21:13.024 --> 21:15.220
What am I gonna say to them, you know?

21:15.692 --> 21:17.745
What? - Fuck you.

21:42.759 --> 21:45.296
Are you sure you
want to work here?

21:47.498 --> 21:49.498
I have no choice.

21:52.000 --> 21:54.504
This place is in a deserted place.

21:55.686 --> 21:58.221
I don't like you
being alone here.

21:58.566 --> 22:00.191
Nothing happens.

22:01.085 --> 22:03.169
What are you doing?

22:03.563 --> 22:07.319
I am coming too. How am I supposed
to see this scum from the inside?

22:24.532 --> 22:26.532
- Hi. - May I help you?

22:26.577 --> 22:28.108
Ben Mary.

22:29.359 --> 22:31.758
I was supposed to start tonight.

22:33.587 --> 22:36.096
Right, right.
Hi, my name is Bobby.

22:36.121 --> 22:37.491
- Hi. - Hi.

22:37.516 --> 22:39.664
- That's Deb. - Hey.

22:39.898 --> 22:42.704
- Do you sell beer?
- Yes, at the back.

22:45.248 --> 22:49.245
